    "THE NOME NUGGET Published Monday Wednesday and Friday by the i NOME PUBLISHING COMPANY NOME ALASKA j Telephone Main 125 P O Box 485 W A BOUCHER _EditorPublisher JAY SMTFH ____Associate Editor EMILY BOUCHER Society Edtior i 2nd Class Matter Application Made in Nome Post Office Subscription Rates Payable hi Advance Debvt red by Carrier in Nome and Little Creek_4150 per month IT p postage paid outside of Nome and vicinity 1600 per year By Carrierper YearNome and Vicinity __1600 CarrierSix MonthsNome and Vicinity_00 MONDAY NOVEMBER 22 1943 THE CRITICAL DAYS The principal threat to a sweeping upsurge of pri vate enterprise after the war as George W Wolf president of United States Steel Export Company sees it is the possible retention by government of war time controls over industry Freedom for business from unnecessary government controls is therefore a postwar must ranking in importance with the other freedoms for which we are fighting Is it possible the day or six months after the war ends that the federal government will relax its ration ing controls its priority system over materials its ppice ceilings its labor freezes its wage stabiliza tion measures and all the other paraphernalia of the war"
